Exam Question 5.5

Write a simple script/code that reads a protein sequence text file in fasta format (Info on the fasta format: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FASTA_format), converts the uppercase letters to lowercase letters, and writes the converted data to a text file, fasta_output.txt.  

The name of the file to be 'read in' should not be hardcoded inside your program but rather inputted as an argument when the program is run.

That is, this is how the program should be implemented/run:

python program.py fasta_input.txt  

(--> should output a text file, fasta_output.txt in your current directory.)

Please copy-paste the following fasta sequence to a text file and name it fasta_input.txt.  Use your favourite editor:

>gi|5524211|gb|AAD44166.1| cytochrome b [Elephas maximus maximus]
   LCLYTHIGRNIYYGSYLYSETWNTGIMLLLITMATAFMGYVLPWGQMSFWGATVITNLFSAIPYIGTNLV
   EWIWGGFSVDKATLNRFFAFHFILPFTMVALAGVHLTFLHETGSNNPLGLTSDSDKIPFHPYYTIKDFLG
   LLILILLLLLLALLSPDMLGDPDNHMPADPLNTPLHIKPEWYFLFAYAILRSVPNKLGGVLALFLSIVIL
   GLMPFLHTSKHRSMMLRPLSQALFWTLTMDLLTLTWIGSQPVEYPYTIIGQMASILYFSIILAFLPIAGX
   IENY


Attach your program file, your input text file (fasta_input.txt), and your output text file (fasta_output.txt) to the corresponding question.

 
